> necessary. I don't have reduction boxes down next to the rear wheels, those
> are in the REALLY old buses (67 or so and older).
> What I cant figure out is why my range seemed to improve when I started
> using 1st and 2nd, instead of sticking in 2nd all the time...
> I made my own tranny/motor mount and modified my tranny shaft, so adding
> the clutch back in isn't a possibility without replacing the tranny.
> If I can keep the bus in 2nd most of the time, that would be great, but
> I've got to keep my range and DOD acceptable.
> Feel free to continue to respond with questions, comments and even
